700666f-a.text:
Bronxwood Avenue (foreground ), north from Waring (right) to Mace Avenues. Also shown, in the background, is Public School No. 89, at the S.E. corner of Colden and Mace Avenues. The view is northeastward.
April 3, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
700666f-a.folder: Bronxwood Avenue & Varing Avenue, Bronx, NY

700665f-b.text:
(1)
Bronxwood Avenue (people thereon), east side, south from Waring Avenue (left) to Astor Avenue, showing Christopher Columbus High School under construction. The view is southeast across Waring Avenue from near Matthews Avenue.
April 3, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A view directly north from Barnes Avenue.
April 3, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
